A cornerstone of Netanyahu’s election promises was to proceed with annexation of West Bank territory. Annexation is illegal under International law and this proposed action has created opprobrium from International actors with one exception that is the Trump administration. The proposed date of July 1st, 2020 has passed. Israel now has a coalition government that has created a degree of stability, politically, for the moment. The Trump Presidency provides the best opportunity for Israel to act and it will only act with the permission of the White House, who are preoccupied with Covid-19, the economy and the upcoming Presidential elections. Russia, a major player in the region, after its annexation of the Crimea would not interfere. The Gulf States appear to be disinterested. Annexation could/would provide further disruption in the Middle East and raise the profile of Palestinians. +/- 30% of Israelis oppose annexation. Without collecting the opprobrium of the International theatre and considering 400,000 Israelis already settled in the West Bank and thereby creating a ‘creeping sovereignty’ there would only be political advantage to a formal annexation. However, due to Covid-19 and criticism of Netanyahu over the handling of the pandemic plus the effect on the country’s economy have redirected attention away from annexation, for the time being. I propose that the Knesset will not pass a bill to annex and/or apply sovereignty before January 1, 2021
